    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Okay, I can scan for .ipython references in the docs.  Do you have a sense of exactly what you think that should look like?  It's now a little harder, since I can't just replace `.ipython` with `.config/ipython`, since that will only be true for systems that use `.config`.\n\nSpeaking of following standards, do we also want to comply with OSX standards, and use ~/Library there?\n"
