    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Okay, I'll start some finding and replacing.\n\ncommand-line unix programs tend to not pay attention to OSX config standards, but real applications do (unless they are bad platform citizens).  With things like the qtconsole, IPython is starting to straddle the gap.  I would say leave .ipython on OSX for now, but add Library support if/when we do implement the split XDG basedir spec.\n"
  },
